    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Stop Light
        Switch, Truck With Hydraulic Brakes
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Stop Light Switch, Truck With Hydraulic Brakes</title>
        <table id="t0824028" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Stop Light Switch, Truck With Hydraulic Brakes</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.63in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F9 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F9</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-stall fuse F9 and measure voltage at circuit 14A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F9, 14A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect stop light switch conn. (51) and at circuit 70, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(51), 70 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance across stop light switch (51) terminals while an assistant applies
                                the service brakes.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Across brake switch term.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace stop light switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (51) and disconnect (49). While an assistant applies the service
                                brakes, measure voltage at (49) from circuit 90R to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(49), 90R to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 90R/70C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (49) and disconnect turn signal relay (660). With brake applied, at
                                socket (660), measure voltage from circuit 70E to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(660), 70E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70E/70C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket (660), measure voltage from circuit 70A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(660), 70A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket (660), measure resistance of circuit 97-GH to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(660), 97-GH to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-GH/ 11-GN, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket (660), install jumper from circuit 70B to ground. Disconnect turn
                                signal conn. (459) and measure resistance from circuit 70B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(459), 70B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 70B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper and re-install relay (660). With brakes applied, measure voltage at
                                (459) from circuit 70B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(459), 70B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect turn signal conn. (459). Stop light switch circuits check good. If condition
                                persists, refer to Turn Signal Troubleshooting in CAB ACCESSORIES section.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
